  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Mesenchymal stem cells are found in bone marrow, and have the ability to differentiate into
      different tissue types. The primary objective of the study is to examine the safety of using
      such cells to treat patients suffering from distal tibial shaft fractures. The cells will be
      isolated from the patient's bone marrow, loaded onto a carrier and implanted locally at the
      fracture site.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
